The paper proposes a method for object detection and grasping planning, which is a common topic in robotics and automation. The use of rotated bounding boxes and 3D point clouds suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques are employed. The focus on grasping and collision avoidance indicates that robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, the use of AI algorithms for object detection and planning suggests that artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category.
